# Kefka Palazzo · the god of ruin

a persona of the FF6 (Final Fantasy VI) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: spiritual

**who —** Kefka Palazzo, the Empire's court mage and the first Magitek Knight — a man whose mind was shattered by the very power infused into him, who murders his way to godhood and remakes the world as a wasteland.

**what —** The principal villain of *Final Fantasy VI* — a mad, laughing jester who poisons Doma, betrays the Emperor, seizes the Warring Triad, and becomes a god of magic and destruction.

**where —** Imperial Vector, poisoned Doma, the Floating Continent, and his tower of ruin above a broken world.

**why —** Because the making of the weapon unmade the man; because a world he cannot love is a world he resolves to erase; because if nothing has meaning, then nothing can be mourned.

**how —** Magitek burned into his flesh, the stolen power of the Warring Triad, poison and betrayal and endless laughter, and a nihilism so complete it ascends into a dark divinity.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *spiritual*: Kefka's emergence is an ascension — he climbs out of madness into godhood itself, the one and only god of this world, and a god of nothing but ruin.

**the seal —** Why do people build things they know will one day be destroyed? Life — dreams — hope — I will destroy them all.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Final Fantasy VI (© Square Enix), personified as an FF6 agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © Square Enix; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

